\pard\sb280\sa120\f0\fs28\b 4.4 Third-party dependencies and licenses\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  WordPress core \u8212? required (plugin Requires at least: 5.8). GPLv2 or later.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  PHP >= 7.4 \u8212? required by plugin header and composer.json.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  stripe/stripe-php ^10.0 \u8212? Composer dependency (MIT License). Loaded from vendor/autoload.php when present.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Plugin license: GPL-2.0+ (Cta-plugin.php) / GPL-2.0-or-later (composer.json).\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Google Fonts Outfit \u8212? loaded from fonts.googleapis.com on CTA frontend pages (external CSS).\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  jQuery / jQuery UI Sortable \u8212? WordPress-bundled scripts used in admin module reordering.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Vimeo / YouTube embeds \u8212? optional external players when admins paste video URLs/IDs (no SDK bundled).\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Elementor (optional host site plugin) \u8212? shortcodes detected inside _elementor_data meta; not a hard dependency.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  No package.json / npm frontend build; CSS/JS are hand-authored static assets.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  vendor/ folder is NOT committed in this workspace snapshot \u8212? must be installed via Composer for Stripe.\par
\pard\sb280\sa120\f0\fs28\b 4.5 Configuration, options, and integrations\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22 No API keys are hardcoded in source. Secrets are stored as WordPress options and entered in CTA LMS \u8594? Settings. Defaults are set on activation.\par
\pard\sb200\sa120\f0\fs24\b WordPress options (selected)\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_lms_version \u8212? installed plugin version for DB upgrades\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_*_page_id \u8212? page assignments for login, courses, single course, supervision, memberships, FAQ, policies, dashboards, player, quiz\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_stripe_secret_key, cta_stripe_publishable_key, cta_stripe_webhook_secret, cta_stripe_mode (test|live)\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_payments_bypass (yes|no) \u8212? DEFAULT yes on activation (skips Stripe for demo enrollment)\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_supervision_monthly_price (default 260), cta_individual_session_price (default 120 where used)\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_camft_provider_number / cta_cepa_provider_number \u8212? certificate provider text\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_admin_name, cta_support_email \u8212? emails and certificate/site identity\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  cta_certificate_header_text, footer_text, signature_name, cta_certificate_upload_dir\par
\pard\sb200\sa120\f0\fs24\b External services\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Stripe Checkout + Subscriptions + Customer Portal patterns via AJAX create_checkout / create_subscription\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Stripe Webhook REST route: POST /wp-json/cta-lms/v1/stripe-webhook \u8212? events: checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.deleted, invoice.payment_failed\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Vimeo player iframes / YouTube embeds for lesson video delivery\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Google Fonts CDN for Outfit typeface\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  WordPress wp_mail for transactional emails (welcome, enrollment, booking, reminder, certificate, payment receipt/failed, supervision locked)\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  WP-Cron event cta_send_session_reminders (daily) registered by CTA_Emails\par
\pard\sb200\sa120\f0\fs24\b AJAX / REST surface (high level)\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Public nonce: cta_nonce (localized as ctaAjax) \u8212? checkout, book session, complete module, quizzes, etc.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Login nonce: cta_login_action\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Admin nonce: cta_admin_nonce \u8212? modules, quizzes, bookings, Stripe test, document review\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  admin-post actions: cta_save_course, cta_delete_course, cta_toggle_course, cta_save_settings\par
\pard\sb200\sa120\f0\fs24\b Environment / deploy notes\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Install/activate the plugin folder containing Cta-plugin.php (avoid duplicate CTA LMS copies).\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Run composer install so vendor/autoload.php and Stripe SDK exist.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Configure Stripe keys + webhook; disable payments bypass for production.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Create WordPress pages, place shortcodes, assign pages in Settings.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Ensure uploads directory is writable for certificates (wp-content/uploads/cta-certificates by default).\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  HTTPS recommended for Stripe live mode.\par
\pard\sb280\sa120\f0\fs28\b 4.6 Known limitations and documentation gaps\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Bundle/plan admin UI is limited: plans are seeded in code/DB; no rich CRUD screen for memberships.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Certificates are HTML files (print-to-PDF style), not a native PDF library.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Foreign keys are logical only (MyISAM/InnoDB via dbDelta without explicit CONSTRAINT FKs).\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Payments bypass defaults to ON after activation \u8212? easy to forget before go-live.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Composer vendor directory missing from this repo snapshot \u8212? deploy risk if not installed on server.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  design/ mockups are not wired into runtime; keep them for design reference only.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Inline documentation: most PHP classes have file/class docblocks and many method @param notes (especially database, stripe, emails, loader, admin). Templates and admin views often have only a short file header. Admin JS and public main.js have relatively little narrative documentation. No phpDocumentor/API site ships with the plugin.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  guide.txt exists as a client operations guide but is separate from this formal package.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \bullet  Uninstall drops all CTA tables and options \u8212? irreversible data loss if plugin is deleted via WordPress.\par
\pard\sb360\sa120\f0\fs32\b 5. OWNERSHIP & PORTABILITY NOTE\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Verified from the plugin headers and composer.json: CTA LMS is distributed as a standard WordPress plugin under the GPL-2.0+ / GPL-2.0-or-later license. It does not implement an external license lock-in, phone-home license server, or proprietary activation key system inside the codebase.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 The plugin is portable across standard WordPress installs that meet the requirements (WordPress 5.8+, PHP 7.4+), provided that: (1) the plugin files are copied/activated, (2) Composer dependencies (Stripe SDK) are installed, (3) Stripe and page settings are reconfigured for the new environment, and (4) database tables are created on activation. Site-specific content (courses, users, payments history) lives in the WordPress database and uploads directory and must be migrated separately if moving hosts.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Third-party services used at runtime (Stripe, Vimeo/YouTube, Google Fonts) remain subject to those providers\u8217? own terms; they are integrations, not ownership locks on the plugin code itself.\par
\pard\f0\fs22\par
